.TH TURBOMOD 1 "2026-06-22" "turbomod 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
turbomod \- moderate Intel Turbo Boost on Linux (intel_pstate)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B turbomod
.I command
.RB [ --persist ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B turbomod
toggles Intel Turbo Boost by writing to the
.I no_turbo
sysfs attribute exposed by the Intel P-State driver at
.IR /sys/devices/system/cpu/intel_pstate/no_turbo .
Disabling Turbo Boost can reduce thermal spikes and produce steadier frame
rates under sustained load.
.PP
Only the
.B intel_pstate
driver is supported. AMD systems and Intel systems using
.B acpi-cpufreq
are not supported.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Show whether Turbo Boost is currently ON or OFF. Does not require root.
.TP
.B enable
Turn Turbo Boost ON (writes no_turbo=0). Requires root.
.TP
.B disable
Turn Turbo Boost OFF (writes no_turbo=1). Requires root.
.TP
.B restore
Re-apply the saved persistent state. Intended to be run at boot by
.BR turbomod-restore.service (8).
Requires root.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --persist
When used with
.B enable
or
.BR disable ,
save the chosen state to
.I /etc/turbomod/state
so it is re-applied on the next boot.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show usage information.
.TP
.BR -v ", " --version
Show the version.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success. Returns 1 if the driver is absent, if root is required
but not present, or if a write could not be verified after being applied.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /sys/devices/system/cpu/intel_pstate/no_turbo
The kernel control file.
.TP
.I /etc/turbomod/state
The saved persistent state (\fBenable\fR or \fBdisable\fR).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Disable Turbo Boost and remember it across reboots:
.B sudo turbomod disable --persist
.SH AUTHOR
Chuck Talk (Nordheim Online / AntiGravity suite).
